{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1dd631eb-2127-4407-a5ca-55de2e5c51f1","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Additional steps:**\n- Update NuGet package references (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.\n- Run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages.\n- Review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API changes affecting your code.\n- Ensure your CI/build agents have the .NET 11 SDK installed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a8e8a8e0-8ac7-4af3-8f47-23e66e47b23c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward informational question - I don't need to look at any files since they've described their setup. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":324,"requestId":"0409:20BD61:6EAB5E:7F3E07:6A052A2F"},"id":"f5931b6f-6682-44b8-a882-27ea467a230a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:49:43.130Z","parentId":"e6b5e1ed-8651-4ce4-ba18-4f1e546e9a52"}
